By Jonathan Nda- Isaiah, President Muhammadu Buhari at exactly 11:51 am and Vice-President Yemi Osinbajo at 11 57 am prompt on Saturday receive the COVID-19 vaccine publicly. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-276153" src="https://i0.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Buhari-Covid-19-vaccine-card.jpg?resize=1024%2C704&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="1024" height="704" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Buhari-Covid-19-vaccine-card.jpg?w=1024&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Buhari-Covid-19-vaccine-card.jpg?resize=600%2C413&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Buhari-Covid-19-vaccine-card.jpg?resize=768%2C528&amp;ssl=1 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> It was preceded by e-registration of President Buhari and Vice President Osinbajo and filling out of their vaccination cards by Executive Director of the National Primary Health Care Development Agency (NPHCDA), Faisal Shuaib. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-276154" src="https://i1.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Buhari-receives-Covid-19-vaccine-.jpg?resize=1024%2C699&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="1024" height="699" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Buhari-receives-Covid-19-vaccine-.jpg?w=1024&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i1.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Buhari-receives-Covid-19-vaccine-.jpg?resize=600%2C410&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i1.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Buhari-receives-Covid-19-vaccine-.jpg?resize=768%2C524&amp;ssl=1 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Vaccination of President Buhari was done by Chief Personal Physician to the President, Dr. Suhayb Rafindadi Sanusi after which he was presented with the e-vaccination card by Dr. Shuaib at 11:59am. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-276155" src="https://i1.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Osinbajo-receives-Covid-19-vaccine-.jpg?resize=1024%2C688&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="1024" height="688" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Osinbajo-receives-Covid-19-vaccine-.jpg?w=1024&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i1.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Osinbajo-receives-Covid-19-vaccine-.jpg?resize=600%2C403&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i1.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Osinbajo-receives-Covid-19-vaccine-.jpg?resize=768%2C516&amp;ssl=1 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> Osinbajo was vaccinated by his personal physician, Dr. Nicholas Audifferen and was also presented with the e-vaccination card by Dr. Shuaib by 11:59am. <img class="aligncenter size-full wp-image-276152" src="https://i0.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Osinbajo-Covid-19-vaccine-card.jpg?resize=1024%2C693&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="1024" height="693" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Osinbajo-Covid-19-vaccine-card.jpg?w=1024&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Osinbajo-Covid-19-vaccine-card.jpg?resize=600%2C406&amp;ssl=1 600w, https://i0.wp.com/leadership.ng/wp-content/uploads/2021/03/Osinbajo-Covid-19-vaccine-card.jpg?resize=768%2C520&amp;ssl=1 768w" sizes="(max-width: 1000px) 100vw, 1000px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The Minister of Health, Dr. Osagie Ehanire, said the jab is painless,  a narrow gauge syringe was used with small quantity injected in the upper arm. He said the after effects are mild and little discomfort follows in the area that was injected. At the brief ceremony were the Secretary to the Government of the Federation (SGF) Mr Boss Mustapha; Minister of Health Dr Osagie Ehanire; Minister of Information and Culture, Alhaji Lai Mohammed; and the Chief of Staff to the President, Professor Ibrahim Gambari. More details later… 